gomodel:SYNGO_4112  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig2F: Immunocytochemistry demonstrates that Snx14 colocalises with dendritic marker MAP2 in dissociated mouse cortical neurons.\nFig2E: Dissociated mouse cortical neurons were transfected with pZsGreen1-Snx14 plasmid and subsequently immunostained with mouse anti-SNX14 antibody and showed colocalisation with ZsGreen1. This indicates the specificity of the anti-SNX14 antibody.\n\n18/01/2021 Dnyanada: The generic term \"synapse\" was used for this annotation as the paper only shows the presence of SNX14 puncta on dendrites.. Experimental description: C57BL/6 mouse (E15.5) cortices were dissected and used for immunocytochemistry." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2916-7616" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2021-01-18" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_4112" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

